<paragraph blockId="25.[151,491,1408,1434]" box="[151,491,1408,1434]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,491,1408,1434]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,491,1408,1434]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[207,314,1408,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tolpia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,314,1408,1434]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">The group comprises 4 species. It is characterised by the following 6 character states; apomorphic character states marked by (apo.):</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,560,1580,1606]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- valve broad at apex (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,1049,1624,1650]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- digitus prominent, asymmetrical; right digitus short and stout (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,695,1667,1693]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- small costal process at base of digitus;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,1179,1710,1736]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- juxta with a prominent ventral mushroom-like process; higher than wide (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,534,1753,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- anellus fused with juxta.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,674,1796,1822]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">- phallus swollen medially (apo.); and</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1494,1865]" box="[151,968,1836,1865]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
- 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[261,273,1836,1850]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">th</superScript>
abdominal segment of female with hollow flaps anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
